<section local-class="hero">
  <div class="hero-body">
    <div local-class="content">
      <div class="container">Hello! I am
        <h1 class="title is-1">
          Max Minkoff
        </h1>
        <h2 class="subtitle is-3">
          Full Stack Web Developer
        </h2>
        <p local-class="bio">
          Highly accomplished <strong>Senior Full-Stack Software Developer</strong>, <strong>Technical Lead</strong>,
          and <strong>Architect</strong> who <strong>delights in collaborating</strong> with stakeholders and team members
          to <strong>create and improve</strong> how people work, learn, and play. That <strong>rare individual</strong>
          able to <strong>explain complex concepts in simple terms</strong> and <strong>translate business needs
            into technical solutions</strong>. <strong>Wharton MBA</strong> with excellent presentation, problem
            solving, and communication skills. <strong>Early-stage startup veteran</strong> happiest in an
            entrepreneurial environment of any size that emphasizes <strong>enduring value over
              short-term payoff</strong>.
            </p>
            <div class="has-addons">
              <a href="https://github.com/mminkoff" target="_maxgithub" local-class="social-button">
                <FaIcon @icon="github" @prefix="fab" />
                Github
              </a>
              <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/max-minkoff/" target="_maxlinkedin" local-class="social-button">
                <FaIcon @icon="linkedin" @prefix="fab" />
                LinkedIn
              </a>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section local-class="section" id="portfolio">
      <div local-class="content">
        <div class="container">
          <div class="section-heading">
            <h3 local-class="section-title">Portfolio</h3>
            <h4 class="subtitle is-5">Some recent and/or interesting projects</h4>
          </div>
          <br>

          <div local-class="portfolio-container">
            <div class="columns">
              <div class="column is-4">
                <Card
                @titleLink="https://goexp.it"
                @title="eThree's goexp.it"
                @headerIconSrc="images/ethree-logo-blue-white.png"
                @headerIconAlt="eThree"
                @imageSrc="images/heather-mitts-goexp-it.png"
                @imageAlt="Heather Mitts on goexp.it"
                >
                Versatile <strong>web-based learning experience platform</strong>, enabling communicators of
                all types to engage consumers with students and customers. Built using
                <strong><a href="https://emberjs.com/" target="_ember">EmberJS</a></strong> and <strong><a href="https://rubyonrails.org/" target="_rails">Ruby on Rails</a></strong> on <strong><a href="https://www.heroku.com/" target="_heroku">Heroku</a></strong>.
              </Card>

              <Card
              @titleLink="https://ourgroove.studio"
              @title="OurGroove.Studio"
              @imageSrc="images/ourgroovestudio.png"
              @imageAlt="ourgroove.studio screenshot"
              >
              An effort to solve the problem of making music together over video conference,
              it allows music leaders to upload MP3s and control synchronized playback on
              any number of remote computers.  Front end prototyped in
              <strong><a href="https://reactjs.org/" target="_react">ReactJS</a></strong> then
              converted to <strong><a href="https://emberjs.com/" target="_ember">EmberJS</a></strong>.
              Back end uses <strong><a href="https://rubyonrails.org/" target="_rails">Ruby on Rails</a></strong>
              on <strong><a href="https://www.heroku.com/" target="_heroku">Heroku</a></strong>.
              Real-time communication uses Websocket via Rails' <strong><a href="https://guides.rubyonrails.org/action_cable_overview.html" target="_rails">Action Cable</a></strong>.
            </Card>
          </div>

          <div class="column is-4">
            <Card
            @title="Cookulus Perfect Cookie Recipes"
            @headerIconSrc="images/cookulus-app.jpg"
            @headerIconAlt="cookulus app"
            @imageSrc="images/Cookulus-Full-screen.jpg"
            @imageAlt="Cookulus screenshot"
            >
            Unique <strong>configurable cookie recipe app</strong>, adjusting recipes
            to deliver crispy or soft, chewy or crumbly, and thin or thick cookies.
            Read what <strong><a href="https://www.newsweek.com/2014/03/14/downloading-delicious-cookie-247931.html
              " target="_newsweek">Newsweek had to say</a></strong> about it.
            </Card>

            <Card
            @titleLink="https://github.com/mminkoff/ember-filestack"
            @title="ember-filestack"
            @headerIconName="github"
            @headerIconPrefix="fab"
            @headerIconSize="2x"
            >
            Ember Add-On providing <strong>file picking, storing, and converting functionality</strong>
            from <a href="https://www.filestack.com/">Filestack</a> using <a href="https://github.com/filestack/filestack-js">filestack-js</a>.
          </Card>

          <Card
          @headerIconSrc="images/uw.png"
          @headerIconAlt="university of washington"
          @titleLink="http://citeseerx.ist.psu.edu/viewdoc/download?doi=10.1.1.75.1545&rep=rep1&type=pdf"
          @target="_thesis"
          @title="Master's Thesis"
          @imageSrc="images/thesis.png"
          @imageAlt="Master's thesis cover"
          >
          My design for a <strong>Virtual Reality system architecture</strong> when I studied
          <strong>Industrial Engineering/Human Factors</strong>
          (i.e. user interface) and had a research fellowship in the
          <strong><a href="https://archive.seattletimes.com/archive/?date=20040409&slug=pacific-phit11" target="_hitl">Human Interface Technology Lab</a></strong> doing VR work.  Turns out
          to have been consistent with the <strong><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Model%E2%80%93view%E2%80%93controller" target="_hitl">MVC Pattern</a></strong>, in that the design included
          independent "displays" (i.e. views) that were responsible for low-latency
          UI, models, and controllers that connected elements to a network-distributed
          database.
        </Card>
      </div>

      <div class="column is-4">
        <Card
        @titleLink="https://schoolsoutindefinitely.com"
        @title="School's Out Indefinitely"
        @headerIconSrc="images/schoolsout-icon.png"
        @headerIconAlt="school's out Indefinitely"
        @imageSrc="images/schoolsout.png"
        @imageAlt="schoolsoutindefinitely.com screenshot"
        >
        Simple website curating virtual learning resources during the 2020 pandemic and beyond.
        Uses <a href="airtable.com">Airtable.com</a> for data storage and otherwise static <a href="https://emberjs.com/" target="_ember">EmberJS</a>
        site hosted on <strong><a href="https://aws.amazon.com/" target="_aws">AWS</a></strong>.  You can <strong><a href="https://github.com/schoolsOut/schoolsOut">view the code here</a></strong>.
      </Card>

      <Card
      @title="This Website"
      @headerIconName="github"
      @headerIconPrefix="fab"
      @headerIconSize="2x"
      @imageSrc="images/maxportfolio.png"
      @imageAlt="max's portfolio website"
      >
      Simple website to highlight some of my projects and demonstrate
      some simple code.  Uses <strong><a href="https://emberjs.com/" target="_ember">EmberJS</a></strong> and <strong><a href="https://bulma.io/" target="_bulma">Bulma CSS Framework</a></strong>, hosted on
      <strong><a href="https://aws.amazon.com/" target="_aws">AWS</a></strong> using <strong>S3</strong> for the website and <strong><a href="https://aws.amazon.com/api-gateway" target="_aws">API Gateway</a></strong>,
      <strong><a href="https://aws.amazon.com/lambda" target="_aws">AWS Lambda</a></strong>, and <strong><a href="https://aws.amazon.com/ses" target="_aws">Simple Email Service</a></strong> for the contact form.
    </Card>

    <Card
    @titleLink="https://bethsholom5781.org"
    @title="Beth Sholom Livestream"
    @headerIconSrc="images/Beth-Sholom-logo.png"
    @headerIconAlt="Beth Sholom Congregation"
    @imageSrc="images/bethsholom5781.png"
    @imageAlt="bethsholom5781.org screenshot"
    >
    Designed, installed, and operated <strong>three-camera remote-controlled livestream</strong>
    for over <strong>1,000 congregants at historic synagogue</strong>.  Created alternate website
    to avoid the inevitable server overload at primary website using <strong><a href="https://emberjs.com/" target="_ember">EmberJS</a></strong>, <strong><a href="https://bulma.io/" target="_bulma">Bulma</a></strong>, and <strong><a href="https://aws.amazon.com/" target="_aws">AWS</a></strong>.
  </Card>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</section>


